On view @ballroommarfa October 6th-March 30th 
 
Perhaps the Truth is inspired by the writings of Wallace Stevens (1879-1955) and the late painter and poet Jesse Murry (1948-1993). The works on view suggest that the truth is not a fixed or absolute concept, but rather something that is shaped by our experiences and shifting perceptions.
Perhaps the Truth is organized by Fairfax Dorn with Daisy Nam, with assistance from Alexann Susholtz.

Tending to our garden—planting housing, 2023

another love letter to @ridgewoodtenantsunion 💌
And a big “fuck you” to AB capstone and it’s luxury tower.
Their “affordable” units will be offered to households earning 130% of the Area Medium Income..which means it’s housing lottery is only open to families earning between $68,160 to $159,640 per year.
Making them completely inaccessible to most working class people. 
I certainly wouldn’t qualify. 
We need fair and affordable housing, we need to rid our city of predatory laws and greedy landlords.
